        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 26 at 4:22PM CDT by NWS Norman OK</headline>
        <description>At 421 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Faxon, moving northeast at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Western Lawton, Chattanooga, Faxon, and southern Fort Sill.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
